- above all the operas - providing the latest information to emerge about some of his most famous pieces. An extensive bibliography supports the entries, which are cross-referenced to enable wider exploration of particular topics. NIGELSIMEONE is a widely respected writer and lecturer on music, with a lifelong interest in Czech music. His books include Janacek's Works (Oxford University Press, 1997, co-authored with John Tyrrell and Alena Nemcová), TheLeonard Bernstein Letters (Yale University Press, 2013), and Charles Mackerras (Boydell Press, 2015, co-edited with John Tyrrell). He is a regular broadcaster on BBC radio.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aOrchestral musicy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aCompositions.  aConductors.  aCzech composer.  aCzech music.  aEthnographer.  aFolksong collector.  aFriends and associates.  aInstrumentalists.  aJanácek's works.  aLeos Janácek.  aLondon.  aMoravian culture.  aNationalist.  aOperas.  aPrague.  aSingers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311143102440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787445086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787445086/original  a978-3-11-143102-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles